quotas.name: Jharkhand Private Seats - Govt Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Jharkhand Private Seats - Govt Quota**

Permanent Residents of Jharkhand (or) Local Residents of Jharkhand.

Local resident has the below criteria   
a. Residing in Jharkhand and should have his ancestor's name registered in the last survey (land). If no land, then Gram Sabha decides based on language, culture and tradition (or)    
b. Residing in Jharkhand for more than 30 years due to any business or employment or other reasons has acquired immovable property (or spouse or children of any such person in b     
c. Officer / Employee of Jharkhand State Govt/Govt recognized institutions or corportations / Govt of India / employed in any statutory post in Govt of Jharkhand or their spouse / children  
d. Born in Jharkhand and completed education up to matriculation in Jharkhand (matric is 10th)

Permanent Residents of Jharkhand (or) Local Residents of Jharkhand.


Local resident has the below criteria


a. Residing in Jharkhand and should have his ancestor's name registered in the last survey (land). If no land, then Gram Sabha decides based on language, culture and tradition (or)
b. Residing in Jharkhand for more than 30 years due to any business or employment or other reasons has acquired immovable property (or spouse or children of any such person in b
c. Officer / Employee of Jharkhand State Govt/Govt recognized institutions or corportations / Govt of India / employed in any statutory post in Govt of Jharkhand or their spouse / children
d. Born in Jharkhand and completed education up to matriculation in Jharkhand (matric is 10th)
